# 🚀 Required Software and Tools

Before starting the **MERN Stack Bootcamp**, students must install and verify the following software on their systems.

## 📥 Mandatory Software

| Software | Purpose | Official Download Link |
|-----------|----------|----------|
| Visual Studio Code (VS Code) | Source Code Editor | https://code.visualstudio.com/ |
| Node.js (LTS Version) | JavaScript Runtime Environment | https://nodejs.org/en/download |
| Git | Version Control System | https://git-scm.com/downloads |
| GitHub | Code Hosting and Collaboration Platform | https://github.com/ |
| MongoDB Community Server | NoSQL Database | https://www.mongodb.com/try/download/community |
| MongoDB Compass | MongoDB GUI Tool | https://www.mongodb.com/products/tools/compass |
| Postman | API Development and Testing Tool | https://www.postman.com/downloads/ |
| Google Chrome | Web Browser for Development and Testing | https://www.google.com/chrome/ |

# 🛠️ Additional Recommended Tools

These tools are not mandatory but are highly recommended for improving productivity and development workflow during the bootcamp.

| Software | Purpose | Official Download Link |
|-----------|----------|----------|
| GitHub Desktop | Graphical Interface for Git and GitHub | https://desktop.github.com/ |
| React Developer Tools | Debugging React Applications | https://react.dev/learn/react-developer-tools |
| Thunder Client | API Testing Inside VS Code | https://www.thunderclient.com/ |
| ESLint | JavaScript Code Quality and Linting | https://eslint.org/ |
| Prettier | Automatic Code Formatting | https://prettier.io/ |
| 7-Zip | File Compression and Extraction Utility | https://www.7-zip.org/ |

> **Important:** Ensure all mandatory software is installed and verified before attending Week 1 sessions to avoid setup delays.
